entry.tran: （问题或词语）哄骗性的，意味深长的，另有所指的
entry.def: A loaded question or word has more meaning or purpose than it appears to have, because the person who uses it hopes it will cause people to respond in a particular way.

example.tran: 言外有言的“性别歧视者”一词

entry.def: If something is loaded with a particular characteristic, it has that characteristic to a very great degree.

example.ex: The President's visit is loaded with symbolic significance...
example.tran: 总统之行充满象征性意义。

example.ex: The phrase is loaded with irony.

entry.tran: （不公平地）有…倾向的，有…偏向的，倒向…的
entry.def: If you say that something is loaded in favour of someone, you mean it works unfairly to their advantage. If you say it is loaded against them, you mean it works unfairly to their disadvantage.

example.ex: The press is loaded in favour of this present government...
The article was heavily loaded against Morrissey.
example.tran: 文章对莫里西非常不利。

means.word_mean: 3. (of statements or questions) charged with associative significance and often meant to mislead or influence;
4. having an abundant supply of money or possessions of value;

list.explanation: 涉有重要含义的言词、意见或暗示

example.en: In spite of your numerous loaded remarks, I do hope you will return sometime when it is convenient.
example.zh: 尽管你提了不少含蓄的意见，我还是希望你能在方便的时候回来。
